text: Ha Jeong-yeon (born 19 May 1984) is a South Korean taekwondo practitioner. She won a gold medal in bantamweight at the 2003 World Taekwondo Championships in Garmisch-Partenkirchen, by defeating Nootcharin Sukkhongdumnoen in the semifinal, and Taylor Stone in the final. ==References== ==External links== * Category:1984 births Category:Living people Category:South Korean female taekwondo practitioners Category:World Taekwondo Championships medalists
